{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, one study found saliency maps to be helpful for incorrect but not for correct AI predictions (Alipour et al., 2020).",
    "A similarly inconclusive picture emerges when the task was to predict the AI prediction.",
    "Two studies reported that saliency maps were not helpful (Chandrasekaran et al., 2018; Ray et al., 2019) and one even reported that they were harmful (Shen & Huang, 2020).",
    "Not a single study reported consistent benefits but several studies found that the effects depended on other factors such as the cognitive requirements underlying the task, AI accuracy or XAI methods (Colin et al., 2022; Fel et al., 2023; Folke et al., 2021; Kim et al., 2022; Lerman et al., 2021; Yang et al., 2022).",
    "The role of these factors will be discussed below."
  ]
}